# HMK Implementation Audit

Audit of `marky/` implementation against `docs/HMK.md`.
175 tests passing as of 2026-06-11.

---

## Bugs

### ~~Bug 1 — Char-range exclusion is silently ignored~~ ✅ Fixed

Exclusions on `char_range`, `named_alpha`, and `full_alpha` are now honored in
`_match_semantic` / `_match_named_alpha` / `_match_full_alpha`. `{a..z,!d..f}`
on `abcdefg` correctly yields `a,b,c,g`. Covered by the exclusion stress tests
in `test_match.py`.

### ~~Bug 2 — Token-position ranges raise CompileError~~ ✅ Fixed

`{cat..dog}` now resolves to a `string_range` node and matches any string
lexicographically between the two endpoints. Equal-length endpoints (the commonvcase) match strings of exactly that length.

---

## Partial / Approximated

### ~~Issue 3 — Grouped-class multi-char tokens flattened~~ ✅ Fixed

`_match_group_class` now matches whole tokens (longest-first) rather than a flat
char set. `{{a,bc},{def,ghi}}` matches `bcghi`; a lone `b` no longer matches
where only `bc` is a member. Single-char groups (`{{a,A},{b,B}}`) still work.

### ~~Issue 4 — `hexi` named alphabet is a no-op~~ ✅ Fixed

`{hexi}` now matches case-insensitive hex digits (`0-9a-fA-F`) via a virtual
branch in `_match_named_alpha`. It remains match-only (not usable as a value
bound — case is ambiguous for positional arithmetic).

### ~~Issue 5 — Virtual alphabets cannot be used as range bounds~~ ✅ Fixed

`ascii` is materialized as a 128-char alphabet, so `{{ascii}..A}` works by
codepoint. `uni` (1.1M codepoints) and `hexi` (case-ambiguous) now raise a clean
`CompileError` instead of an uncaught `ValueError`.

### ~~Issue 6 — Chained `{{.}}` deferred resolution not implemented~~ ✅ Fixed

Steps are now classified as _pattern_ or _template_ (a template contains `{{…}}` nodes). `execute` is split into two recursions in `engine/__init__.py`: `_run` (top-level extract → `list[str]`, drops non-matches) and `_transform` (in-place replace → `str`, preserves surrounding text). A template's `{{.}}` is deferred: it substitutes `_transform(remaining_chain, match.text)`. Filter chains (`pattern => … => template`) are unchanged; alternating `pattern => template => pattern => template` now works. Covered by `test_integration.py::test_chain_deferred_*`.

---

## Docs Issues

### ~~Docs Issue 7 — North Star patterns have literal spaces~~ ✅ Fixed

Both the Markdown-heading and IPv4 North Star examples used decorative spaces
that HMK treats as literal text. They are now written in compact form and a
note explains whitespace significance. All three North Star patterns
(Markdown, IPv4, Bitcoin) verified to run verbatim from the spec.

---

## What Aligns Well

- **τ/α cardinality model** — singleton detection, parse-time evaluation, and
  bound classification all behave exactly as specified.
- **Repetition by equality** — `{a..z}[3]` requires `aaa`, `bbb`, etc., not any
  mix; backtracking longest-first works.
- **No-anchor scanning** — no implicit start/end anchors; engine scans left to
  right and returns all non-overlapping matches, consistent throughout.
- **Named alphabets** (`dec`, `hex`, `HEX`, `hexi`, `b32`, `b58`, `b64`, `b85`,
  `ascii`) — all match correctly.
- **Value-range arithmetic** (`upper_bound`, `lower_bound`, `bounded_range`,
  `string_range`) — including exclusions on numeric ranges.
- **Padding** (`{N: expr}`, `{: expr}`) — fixed and variable-width both work.
- **Captures** — 0-based left-to-right numbering, dot-notation sub-captures,
  `{{#N}}` count references all correct.
- **Separators** (`<<sep>>`) — lazy span, split semantics, `<<\n>>` on full input.
- **Transformers** (`=>`) — two-step chains (the common case) work correctly.
- **Singleton constructors** (`{z}[33]` as τ bound) — cardinality-based
  classification is implemented and tested.
